    Blood endotoxin levels as biomarker of non-alcoholic fatty liver disease: a systematic review and meta-analysis.
 Our results support blood endotoxin levels as relevant diagnostic biomarker for NAFLD, both for disease detection as well as staging during disease progression, and might serve as surrogate marker of enhanced intestinal permeability in NAFLD.
